article.headline: Lady Raiders cruise
article.linkText: Texas Tech muscles up on Oral Roberts
article.story:
LUBBOCK, Texas (AP) -- Cisti Greenwalt had 18 points, 14 rebounds
and blocked seven shots to lead No. 13 Texas Tech to a 79-46
victory over Oral Roberts on Thursday night.

Greenwalt had her fourth double-double in five games for the
Lady Raiders (5-1). Greenwalt is the Big 12 Conference career
leader in blocked shots with 219.

Elisha Turek led Oral Roberts (3-2) with 10 points, well below
her average of 22.8.

Alesha Robertson added 15 points and LaToya Davis 14 for Texas
Tech, which scored 26 off turnovers.

The Lady Raiders, who led 40-22 at halftime, shot 42 percent.
Oral Roberts finished with 36 percent.
